The Fundamental Identity  

The classical NB obeys a simple combinatorial identity known as the
"fundamental identity", or simply "FI".  If you attempt to totally
antisymmetrize  commuting entities chosen from among  possibilities,
you obviously obtain zero.  As a consequence,
 
